Based on this, plasma of blood collected from a group of recovered COVID-19 patients was administered to 10 patients in high-risk condition.
Their symptoms improved within 24 hours, and the burden of inflammation and pathogenesis decreased, and the concentration of bioflavonoids in the blood improved.
